{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 N.I.N.A. - Nighttime Imaging \u8216'N\u8217' Astronomy Changelog\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If N.I.N.A. helps you in your journey for amazing deep sky images, please consider a donation. Each backer will help keeping the project alive and active.\line More details at nighttime-imaging.eu/donate/\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Version 3.2\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Bugfixes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Sky Atlas constellation filter is no longer failing to find some of the objects that are part of the selected constellation\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Improvements\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The device chooser will now show a stored device id that is currently not available as an \u8220"Offline device\u8221" instead of showing \u8220"No Device\u8221" to differentiate having no device selected versus a saved device that is currently unavailable\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab ZWO EAF is now available as a native driver\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Framing assistant sky annotation options are now saved to the active profile\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Looping mode is no longer started when NINA connects to PHD2.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Commandline Options\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The following command line options have been added\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 -g, --disable-hardware-acceleration        Disables UI hardware acceleration\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Plugin Development\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 AssemblyLoadContext\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Plugins are now loaded within separate {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/dependency-loading/understanding-assemblyloadcontext"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
AssemblyLoadContexts
}}}
\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab This change will isolate third party plugin dependencies so that one plugin having a different version of the same third party library will no longer cause issues\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab No changes to existing plugins are required\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Version 3.1 Hotfix 2\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Improvements\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The hard disk space scan is no longer put into the log header and thus blocking the application start for the duration of the scan. This check can take a bit when network drives are mapped where the initial connection to them can take a while. Instead the check will done asynchronously and put into an info log statement.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Quicker switching between single-exposure and stream mode on QHY cameras, bringing improved responsiveness when using the Speckle or Lucky Imaging plugins.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Improved accuracy of estimated time display for Wait If Sun/Moon altitude instructions as well as Loop while Sun/Moon altitude conditions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Improved the dock panel layout for flat panels inside the imaging tab when smaller sized\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added a new instruction {\f1 Save Sequence} to be able to automatically save the sequence during runtime inside the advanced sequencer\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab In Framing Assistant the \u8220"Annotate DSO\u8221" and \u8220"Annotate Grid\u8221" buttons will keep their state when resizing or reloading the framing image\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab SITELEV keyword is now populated from Options > Astrometry instead of the mount\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Legacy sequencer now also shows validation issues for target startup actions like slew, center & rotate\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Weather Underground client now knows about wind gust and rain rate, and has increased decimal precision for all supported weather statistics\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Bug Fixes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When using CFitsio to save files, if the file name contains a parenthesis, it will no longer fail to save. parenthesis are special characters for CFitsio and will thus replaced with an underscore.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab In some special cases the {\f1 AutoFocus After Exposures} trigger was no longer firing. The trigger logic is adjusted and should handle these cases properly now.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fixed an issue where sky flat exposure time compensation was going into the wrong direction\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The color boxes in the color schema settings now show their true color also when they are not clickable\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Text color when opening the additional options of Sequence Instructions using the three dots are now using the same color as the instruction text itself\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When using the {\f1 Cool Camera} instruction, the camera\u8217's failure to reach the target setpoint now results in a sequence error event. An example cause would be the camera\u8217's cooling progress stalling (moving < 0.5\u176?C over 2 minutes) while the cooler is at 100% power due the ambient temperature being too hot to reach the desired setpoint.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fixed a display issue in the mini sequencer where the sequence container header was indented too much.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Messagebox instruction now automatically closes when a loop will interrupt the instruction set where the message box is placed inside\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Improved input behavior for topocentric coordinates where sometimes a small rounding issue lead to incorrect display when cloning instructions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When using a dome with the dome follower, a timeout during dome synchronization will no longer cancel the remaining steps after a meridian flip\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab QHY Cameras:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab The TEC setpoint and state is now preserved when switching between single-exposure and stream mode.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab The list of available cameras will now properly update when one camera is replaced by a different one.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When dome option to \u8220"close on unsafe conditions\u8221" was selected it is no longer commanding the closure multiple times when switching to unsafe and instead properly waits for the first call to finish\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Version 3.1 Hotfix 1\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Improvements\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab On the equipment camera tab, the cooler chart axes are now annotated with their units of measure. The temperature axis has been moved to the right side.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The meridian flip pop-up no longer shows guiding related items when no guider is connected or when direct guider is connected\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Bug Fixes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fixed an issue where a sequence item was sometimes not marked as failed on error\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Cancelling a connection attempt to switch equipment will no longer result in duplicate switches upon a subsequent successful connection\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Handling of unresponsive sequence instructions is no longer applied to instruction sets and thus preventing multiple error messages and isolating the issue to the specific instruction in question\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Native autofocus: When only one star is detected, the routine will no longer fail with the error that there is not enough HFR spread\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Prevent an edge case where the time condition did not cancel the remaining instructions following an instruction that did not fit into the remaining time, even though those subsequent instructions would fit within the available time\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Version 3.1\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Behavioral Changes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Loop while unsafe condition will not be skipped anymore when the safety monitor is not connected but instead it is assumed that the state is unsafe and the loop for it will run\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Center after drift will now only trigger when the next instruction is a LIGHT frame exposure (similar to autofocus triggers). This will not affect the background solving to determine the drift distance\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Sky Atlas Images are now generated from the Offline Sky Map Cache. The \u8220"Sky Atlas Image Repository\u8221" option has been removed as it is now fully superseded by the Offline Sky Map Cache.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The image saving method has been updated from a two-step process (writing a temporary file and then moving it to the destination) to a single write process. Now, the image is processed first and then written directly to the destination.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab This change addresses issues on some systems where cloud sync file listeners, antivirus software, and similar processes block file access.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab For exposures lasting multiple seconds, there will be no noticeable performance loss.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab For short burst exposures, to achieve similar performance as before, adjust the file save queue size. Go to Options > General > Advanced > Image Save Queue Size and set the queue size to greater than one. Note that this setting will require more application memory.\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Improvements\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Allow camera cooling values down to -200\u176?C instead of restricting it to -50\u176?C\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Disallow opening the ASCOM setup screens when a device is connected\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The setup screens for devices now run in separate non-blocking STA (Single-Threaded Apartment) Threads\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab As a result, you can open ASCOM setup screens without compromising the main application\u8217's responsiveness.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab However, please note that you must close the setup screen for the specific device before being able to connect to it.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Offline Framing Gridlines for right ascension now use a better increment of 5, 10, 15 , 30, 60 minutes on the scale\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Alpaca Devices can now open their setup in a web browser when clicking on the setup button next to the device chooser\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Image History axis selection now persists across sessions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Improved handling of unresponsive sequence instructions after cancellation: Now continues sequence execution if an instruction fails to react to cancellation within two minutes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A warning message is now displayed in the lower right corner of the application when trace logging is enabled. This warning highlights to the user that trace logging is active, ensuring it is not accidentally left on. Trace logging should only be enabled for debugging specific issues due to its potential impact on performance and log file size.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab USB device connection and disconnection are now logged with detailed information including Device ID, PNP Device ID, Description, Name, Manufacturer, Service and Status\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab On Camera Download Failed the gain and filter is now displayed properly when using default gain values and current filter input\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The documentation is now included as an offline page with the installer.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Additionally, the documentation is now integrated directly into the application. You can access it by clicking the book icon in the lower-left corner, instead of opening it in a browser window.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Furthermore some sections of the application now offer a direct popup to their respective section in the manual by clicking the book icon\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The application version number is now shown in the title bar of a notification. Furthermore the notification window size is slightly increased in width.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Bugfixes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fix Center instruction to consider plate solver gain\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fixed colors of Flat Wizard Tabs to use same styling as other similar tabs in the app\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fixed that an incorrect flag was evaluated for the mount capability of PulseGuiding\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fixed an issue in TimeCondition where the time would be overridden to current time\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When polling the SafetyMontior for \u8220"IsSafe\u8221" and an error occurs it will now always assume unsafe conditions instead of using the last known value\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When hovering over the list of plugin entries in the plugin tab the complete row is now clickable to select the entry instead of just the text area\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Alpaca devices that are no longer responding are now properly recognized and disconnected\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Previously, during the exposure time or brightness determination in the flat wizard, along with its corresponding sequencer instructions, all images were retained in memory, leading to a spike in memory consumption. This issue has been addressed; now, only the most recent image will be kept in memory.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Offline Sky Cache will now always find the relevant tiles for small field of views.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fixed an issue where Auto Brightness Flat and Auto Exposure Flat would apply an incorrect value range when used via the flat wizard\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab An autofocus that happened before any LIGHT frame was saved is now registered properly in the history and considered for triggerevaluation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Removed an unnecessary 5 seconds delay after executing an external script\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Autofocus runs with current Profile-ID are now shown after changing the profile\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fixed interpretation of pixel scale value in PinPoint\u8217's solve results\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Plugin Development\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 New Feature: {\f1 IMessageBroker} Interface\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Introduction of {\f1 IMessageBroker} Interface:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A new {\f1 IMessageBroker} interface has been added to facilitate inter-plugin communication.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab This interface allows plugins to publish and subscribe to messages of type {\f1 NINA.Plugin.Interfaces.IMessage}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Promotes loose coupling between plugins by allowing them to communicate without direct references to each other.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Publishing Messages:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Plugins can now inject the IMessageBroker interface to publish messages.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Messages can carry various metadata, including:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab SenderId: The unique identifier of the sender plugin.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Sender: The name of the sender plugin.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab SentAt: The UTC timestamp when the message was sent.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab MessageId: A unique identifier for each message.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Topic: The topic or intent of the message.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Content: The generic body of the message.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Additional metadata such as Priority, Expiration, CorrelationId, and custom headers.\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Subscribing to Messages:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Plugins can subscribe to specific message topics via the {\f1 IMessageBroker}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When a message is published to a topic, all subscribed plugins will receive and process the message asynchronously.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Event Additions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Device mediators have been enhanced with numerous new events that subscribers can monitor following an action performed by the device (e.g., mount slewing, cover opening, etc.)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Platesolve Measurements\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The CenteringSolver\u8217's substeps, which were previously opaque, are now measured individually.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Results of these measurements are provided via {\f1 Measurement} data structure alongside the plate solve result.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 New Control \u8220"Browser\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab NINA.WPF.Base now includes the dependencies to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/webview2/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
WebView2
}}}
\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Using this dependency you can embed a browser into the application\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Version 3.0\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Important Changes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Rotation values in N.I.N.A. have been updated to use the counter-clockwise notation, aligning with the common \u8220"East of North of North Celestial Pole\u8221" standard used in most astronomical applications. Existing templates, targets, and other saved items from previous versions will be automatically migrated to reflect this change.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab ZWO: Persistent device IDs (Aliases) are now supported for ZWO cameras and filter wheels. If one is already set in either of these devices and has not yet connected to it under NINA 3.0, the device will need to be selected again and connected in NINA\u8217's Camera or Filter Wheel equipment selection list. This change makes it easier to support setups where multiple ZWO cameras and filter wheels are present.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Device IDs are limited to 8 ASCII characters in length.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab ZWO EFWs must have firmware version 3.0.9 or later to support storing persistent device IDs.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The command line options have been revisited. Previously {\f1 /profileid <profile id>} was available. This has been changed to {\f1 --profileid <profile id>}. See below for more details.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Flat Wizard logic has been revamped and can now also be used inside the sequencer. See below for more details.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The \u8220"Loop for time\u8221" condition and \u8220"Wait for time\u8221" instruction have been redesigned. When selecting dawn or dusk times, the rollover will now occur at sunrise or sunset, respectively. For example, when dusk is selected, the rollover will happen at dawn.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The native driver for Pegasus Ultimate Power Box v2 has been removed. The Pegasus Unity ASCOM driver supersedes this implementation and should be used instead.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The native driver for PrimaLuceLab EAGLE has been removed. The EAGLE ASCOM Switch Driver supersedes this implementation and should be used instead.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab SGP Server API has been removed from the core application. Instead this is available as a plugin via \u8220"SGP Server Emulation\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Touptek, RisingCam, Altair, MallinCam, OgmaCam and OmegonCam now support HDR modes if available. The \u8220"High Conversion Gain\u8221" toggle has been removed and instead this is controlled via ReadoutModes!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab DARKFLAT has been removed from the selection of image types. They really are just DARKs and are classified as such. Previous saved sequences and templates will be automatically migrated.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 .NET 8\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The application has transitioned to .NET 8. This is not merely a version upgrade from the previously used .NET Framework 4.8. Instead, .NET 8 is rooted in .NET Core, representing a complete rewrite of the .NET Framework by Microsoft. This marks a significant technical advancement for N.I.N.A.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Plugins from previous versions are disabled. They must be patched by the plugin authors and targeted specifically for the new version to ensure compatibility with .NET 8.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Improvements\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The Profile Chooser will now be displayed before the application fully initializes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab This change also fixes the issue that sequence templates are loaded from the first profile when switching it in the chooser instead of the one being chosen\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The guider tab will now also show the dither pixels translated to the main camera based on the guider pixel scale reported by the connected guiding application\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab N.I.N.A. will attempt to synchronize the mount\u8217's clock with that of the computer\u8217's. Not all mount drivers support this feature. A warning will be displayed if the difference between the clocks is more than 10 seconds and the mount time cannot be set\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab ZWO: Native driver for ZWO EFWs now supports setting the Unidirectional option as well as initiate a calibration run.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab ZWO: The native driver for ZWO cameras now supports managing the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://astronomy-imaging-camera.com/tutorials/everything-you-need-to-know-about-astrophotography-pixel-binning-the-fundamentals/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
Mono Bin
}}}
 feature of models with color sensors.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab QHY: Added support for 6x6 and 8x8 bin modes to the QHY native driver. This applies to camera models that support these modes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab GNSS devices: Support for retrieving site location information has been expanded to enable different types of sources:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab NMEA serial GNSS devices\par}
