{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 New Advanced Sequencer\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab In this area a custom sequence can be built completely from scratch by individual small building blocks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Each user has a different flow of how a sequence should look like. This advanced planning can serve most requirements that a user might have.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The building blocks consist of these categories\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i Instruction Sets}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab These sets group together different instructions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Templates can be generated out of these sets to be used later with the same parameters\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i Instructions}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab These are the individual steps to automate the sequence\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Each item has a different operation, like switching to a filter or taking an exposure\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i Trigger}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Triggers are part of an instruction set and are evaluated after each instruction is processed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab They have certain conditions that are checked and when these are fullfilled the triggers will fire\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Examples for these are autofocus after certain parameters, merdian flip or dithering after an amount of exposures\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Triggers are always cascading. So a trigger on an instruction set on a higher level than the currently executed instruction set will also be evaluated\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i Loop Conditions}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab These conditions are attached to an instruction set and drive the behavior of the set\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab As long as a condition is fullfilled, the instruction set will be looped\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Once a condition is not fullfilled anymore, all remaining instructions inside an instruction set will be skipped\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Loop conditions are always cascading. So a conditions on an instruction set on a higher level than the currently executed instruction set will also be evaluated\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i Templates}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Each instruction set can be saved as a template\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab These templates store all info that has been set inside the instruction set and can be restored for later usage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Furthermore these will be stored physically inside the default sequence folder and can be reorganized there\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Sub folders inside the default sequence folder are possible and will group these templates together\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i Targets}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Each Deep Sky Object Sequence be saved as a target\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab These target store all info that has been set inside the deep sky object sequence and can be restored for later usage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Furthermore these will be stored physically inside the default sequence folder and can be reorganized there\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab For more details on the usage refer to the documentation\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 New Plugin Tab\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab With the introduction of the advanced sequencer, a sequence can be planned with individual building blocks. These blocks have been designed to work like small plugins that will be initialized on startup. This opens up the possibility for specialized custom plugins that can be installed independently on demand.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab To manage these custom plugins for the advanced sequencer a new application tab page has been introduced. There a user can setup and see all installed plugins as well as having the possiblity to see, install and update plugins from the official online plugin repository.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Plugins can currently hook into the advanced sequencer, add new dock panels in the imaging tab or add different behaviors for autofocus, star detection and star annotation. More areas to be pluggable are planned for the future.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The main benefit of these plugins are the possibility to create very specialized behavior, that would only benefit by a smaller user base, without cluttering the application with these capabilities for users that do not need this special behavior.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Framing Tab\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Instead of sending the current target to the sequencer, the user will be prompted to either choose the simple sequencer or directly send the target to the new advanced sequencer while also being able to choose from different templates\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Replacing of the complete targets is removed, as this is not necessary.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Possibility to manually enter target rotation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A new multi action button replaces the slew button. This button can either \u8220"slew\u8221", \u8220"slew and center\u8221" or \u8220"slew, center and rotate\u8221" your current framing\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Improved precision when dragging the rectangle around, especially for longer distances\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added a new option to preserve the alignment when being far away from celestial equator where panels won\u8217't be perfectly aligned to a rectangle anymore when having the same rotation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Visually show the misalignment when having the same rotation for each panel when being further away from the celestial equator\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added a new grid showing the mosaic panel coordinates and orientations\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added a center dot for the framing rectangle\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A new toggle is available to toggle the sky background instead of the framing rectangle\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The Sky Object Annotation will now properly draw elliptical objects when position angle and size information is available instead of always showing them as circular\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Offline Sky Map can now show images from the cache (x64 only). The \u8220"Sky Atlas Image Repository\u8221" could unfortunately not be lifted for this, but existing images from the cache in framing will can be used.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Imaging Tab - Sequence Panel\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab As the new sequencer has a dynamic operation mode, the old summary is not feasible anymore when using the advanced sequencer\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Instead the sequence panel will show a minimized representation of the advanced sequence, where you can see the instructions with basic details\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When using the simple sequencer the old style will still be shown instead\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 New hardware support\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 SkyGuard\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Integration of SkyGuard in NINA\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added of SkyGuard Guider and its setup\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Implementation of the Connect, Disconnect, StartGuiding, StopGuiding and Dither methods\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 MGEN3\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Full control of the MGEN3 by mirroring the controller display into N.I.N.A.\u8217's user interface\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Automatic power-on when connecting\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Starts guiding on sequence start\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Performs calibration and star auto-selection when required\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Displays star drift during guiding in a graph\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Dithering during sequencing\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 MetaGuide\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab MetaGuide is now available as an option for a guiding application\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 SVBony\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added a native driver for SVBony cameras. Tested with SV305M Pro and SV405CC.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 SBIG\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added a native driver for SBIG cameras.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 MallinCam\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added native driver for MallinCam cameras.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Risingcam\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Native support for Risingcam added\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Player One\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Native support for Player One Cameras\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 ASCOM Dome\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab ASCOM Domes are supported throughout the application\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Natively provides azimuth synchronization with the telescope, so no additional applications are needed (such as ASCOM Device Hub)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Lateral offsets supported, enabling side-by-side telescope setups\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab When synchronization is enabled, telescope slews wait for the dome to synchronize before next actions, such as imaging and plate solving\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Homes the dome prior to parking, which can improve the reliability of arriving precisely at the park location. This can be important if a shutter motor battery charges in the park position\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Dome actions provided in the new sequencer\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Enable dome synchronization\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Open/Close shutter\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Park dome\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 ASCOM CoverCalibrator\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab With the ASCOM Platform Version 6.5 a new type of interface was added called \u8220"CoverCalibrator\u8221".\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab These are basically flat panel devices which will now be available to choose from in the application under the flat panel section\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 ASCOM SafetyMonitor\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab An ASCOM device to monitor safe conditions for an imaging run\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab These devices can be used inside the sequencer to interrupt an imaging run, when they report unsafe conditions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Option to automatically close the dome shutter immediately when the safety monitor reports unsafe conditions\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Native support for Atik EFW2/3 and internal Filterwheels\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The integrated filter wheels for Atik cameras like the Atik One 9.0 are now natively supported\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab This allows usage of native camera drivers for Atik cameras with integrated filter wheels\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The Atik EFW2 and 3 can also be natively connected without using the ASCOM driver\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Improvements for Altair, Touptek, Omegaon, Mallincam and Risingcam native drivers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Native driver implementation unified for a common interface, as the underlying SDKs are similar\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Additive binning can be turned on\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fan speed can be controlled when available\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Binning info for these cameras are now properly inserted into Metadata\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 PHD2\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Dither will be skipped when not actively guiding or the guide star was lost\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Settle time will now correctly be considered when starting guiding\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Guiding start timeout will not consider calibration time and will also be used when \u8220"Guiding start retry\u8221" is off\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Guiding start retry will not retry more than three times to prevent an infinite loop\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A ROI percentage can now be set for PHD2 to be considered during guidestar search\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Profiles can now be switched from the list of available PHD2 profiles\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Device-related Improvements\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i Canon}: Automatically send request to increase shutdown time, when camera is about to shutdown\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i Nikon}: Fixed an issue where cancelling an exposure would lead to unexpected bulb exposure times\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Flat Device Brightness is no longer expressed in percentage, but rather in the absolute values the flat panel supports\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Flat Device {\i trained brightness levels} will be {\i automatically migrated} from percentage to absolute values {\i after first flat panel device connection}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Filter Wheel List of Filters are now all using the list from the profile instead of having a mix of filters from the ASCOM driver and those from the profile. De-Sync of these lists can\u8217't happen anymore.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Some mount drivers have reversed primary and secondary axis implementation for manual movements. Now a reverse flag is available to manually correct this behavior.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab ASCOM Camera driver can now handle odd sensor width & height for mono sensors. A setting to enable this new behavior is available.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab ASCOM connection and disconnection logic is now unified between all devices to ensure same bahvior\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab ASCOM connection that is lost without any raised error will now be tried to be reconnected one time. If an error happens due to that the application will disconnect like before.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab ASCOM get and set methods use a unified logic to ensure same behavior for all devices\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i FLI}: Background flush is now disabled prior to readout to prevent a hung readout\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i FLI}: Filter wheel driver now removes any extraneous {\f1 /} character from single-filter positions on CenterLine filter wheels\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i MGEN2} now supports unattended guide star selection and calibration, and automatic meridian flips\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Altair, MallinCam, Omegon, RisingCam and ToupTek subsampling is now available\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Application Improvements\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 General\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The application distribution is now code signed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Application window will now remember its placing and state\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Application initialization is utilizing more parallel processing to startup faster.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Application logs are vastly improved to log a lot more info of what is happening at the various levels. INFO level will also contain a lot more info of what is happening at a high level.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab It is now possible to change the application font in the options\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab It is now possible to start, resume and cancel sequences from the preview window\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Options menu has been restructured to adhere to the Equipment layout\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Auto-focus is now its own tab in the Options menu\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Empty gain and offset settings will now always reflect the settings set in Equipment - Camera (valid for imaging, sequence and auto-focus)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Any active field of view or ocular rotation angle is now imported along with coordinates from Stellarium and TheSky X\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab New translation for Czech (\u268?e\u353?tina) has been added\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab New translation for Norwegian Bokmal (Norsk bokm\u229?l) has been added\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab New translation for Korean (\u54620?\u44397?\u50612?) has been added\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Can send the sequencer target coordinates to the Framing Wizard\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Improved Meridian Flip reliability by retrying when changing the pier or slewing close to the meridian fails. NINA now provides a warning suggesting to increase the meridian wait time if this hapens\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Guider settings moved to the guider equipment page making them easier to find and exposing only settings relevant for each type of guider\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Connect all button now connects all devices in a sequential order to prevent collisions with com port scanning that could happen\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab After hitting connect all button, it will show highlighted and when hit again it will disconnect all devices instead\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Meridian Flip now allows for a time range instead of a single point in time to allow for less time lost\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Some areas where the user interface was clipped on lower resolutions (down to 720p) are now showing all details\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Telescope panel in imaging tab now shows an indicator when the telescope is not unparked\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Telescope Park action will now wait for the scope to reach park position\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Profile chooser on startup can now be re-activated in options again once it is disabled\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Guiding gets stopped before any telescope-moving sequencer command gets executed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Gain/Offset fields will now show the default values as a hint text, rather than being populated inside the textbox itself. Having this approach, a user can directly enter specific values without having to clear the default value first.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The imaging tab layout is now saved per profile, instead of one layout for all profiles\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Most options and values now also display a unit of measure if applicable\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Weather information in equipment tab now shows correct wind direction.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Various layout improvements and redesign of controls\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Flat Wizard page controls are streamlined with the rest of the application by replacing the sliders with steppers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When closing a dock panel in the imaging tab and reopening it again, the position is properly restored\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Cooling charts in the camera equipment tab have been merged into one single chart with the history size increased from 100 to 1000\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab On web requests the user-agent header is now filled properly\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab An autofocus indicator in the HFR history will no longer change the Y-Axis scale\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The automatic roll over to a blind solver can now be switched off in the plate solver tab\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab For the first image in an image view control, the image will now be shown as size to fit instead of 1:1 by default\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Profiles can now store an arbitrary description\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Pixel inspector on imaging tab (by holding right click on an image) now also includes min, max and mean of the pixel area\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Subsampling\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The sub sample button above the image panel has been removed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab In the imaging camera control panel when subsampling is enabled a new control will be visible to adjust the subsampling directly there\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab This should be more intuitive to use and does not require a certain order of operations and an active non sub sampled image to set up\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Local Horizon Display\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab It is now possible to define a custom horizon to be used and displayed in the altitude charts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Using these custom horizons will make target planning a lot more convenient when only a portion of the sky is available\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The horizon file consists of a simple mapping of azimuth to altitude values\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 The sky atlas has a new entry for altitude filter to filter for the object to be above the horizon for the specified time range\sa180\par}
