{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Sky Atlas\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The sky atlas has a new entry for altitude filter to filter for the object to be above the horizon for the specified duration\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Filter for time from/through is now only showing time without a day\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Altitude filter is changed to use a duration instead of a start and end time\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Moon distance is now shown in the list for each object. Furthermore a new filter is added to filter by moon distance.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Auto-focus system\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Auto-focus can now have different settings for gain, offset and binning per filter\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When using an autofocus filter with offsets this filter will now also be used for the first and last measurement instead of the filter prior to starting the auto focus\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab During an auto-focus run while taking an image, if the download fails it will be automatically retried up to two times to try to recover\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A new optional setting R\u178? threshold can now be set. When this threshold is non-zero, the autofocus run has to fullfill a minimum required R\u178? - {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coefficient_of_determination"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
Coefficient of determination
}}}
 - above this threshold to be considered as successful.\sa180\par}
