{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Various spelling and grammar fixes throughout the application\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added or clarified several missing tool tips\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Gain/Offset controls now display the current gain/offset the camera is set to when no gain/offset is specified\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Auto-focus system\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Auto-focus has been enhanced to support multiple curve fitting methodologies:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Parabolic fitting, weighted by standard deviation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Hyperbolic fitting, weighted by standard deviation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab A combination of parabolic or hyperbolic fitting, with trend lines. The averages of fitting minimum and trend line intersection are then used\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A contrast detection auto-focus routine has been added. Instead of analyzing stars to determine the point of best focus, the routine will analyze the overall contrast of the image using various contrast detection methods. A Gaussian fit is then performed on the obtained focus points. On some systems, this process can employ shorter exposure times compared to Star HFR and produce results faster\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The single backlash compensation system has been improved and split into two selectable behaviors:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Absolute, where the focuser is moved in or out by the specified number of steps plus any additional steps for backlash. This is the same system that has existed before\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Overshoot, a new method, where the focuser is moved in or out by the requested number of steps, plus any \u8220"overshoot\u8221" number of steps, and is then moved in the opposite direction by the same number of \u8220"overshoot\u8221" steps. This is suitable for optical systems such as SCTs, which might benefit from this method in order to eliminate mirror flop\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The \u8220"Crop Ratio\u8221" setting has been changed to \u8220"Inner Crop Ratio\u8221", and an additional \u8220"Outer Crop Ratio\u8221" setting has been added. This allows users to define a centered ROI, or a centered \u8220"square doughnut\u8221", which will be used by star detection. This allows for avoiding stars in the center and at the edges of the camera\u8217's FOV when a frame is analyzed during auto-focus\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab HFR calculation is now computed using the mean background surrounding the star instead of the entire image\u8217's mean\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab HFR calculation has been enhanced to provide more accurate results, especially for imaging systems that have central obstructions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Auto-focus trend lines now use a weighted fit based on HFR standard deviation in each image rather than an unweighted fit. This provides much better slopes and final derived focus point\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A filter for use in auto-focusing can be set if \u8220"Use filter offsets\u8221" is set to true. When defined, the auto-focus routine will use the specified filter instead of the current imaging filter. Initial baseline HFR and final HFR (used to determine whether the auto-focus run was successful) will still use the intended imaging filter.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added the ability to keep guiding active during auto-focus operations\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The auto-focus routine has been changed so that it doesn\u8217't attempt to measure the focus twice for the same point on the curve\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If it is turned on, a focuser driver\u8217's internal temperature compensation feature is now turned off before an auto-focus operation starts and is turned back on when the operation completes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Meridian Flip now has an option to trigger an auto-focus operation after a meridian flip while a sequence is running\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Backlash compensation will no longer be applied more than once if focuser movement is canceled during focuser settle time\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab An auto-focus operation will not be performed if it might interfere with a pending meridian flip\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab All auto-focus operations and their data points are now logged to their own JSON-formatted file located in {\f1 %LOCALAPPDATA%\\NINA\\AutoFocus}. This allows one to retrace what was measured at a later time\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Sequencer\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Parameters in rows that are added to a sequence will now default to the parameters specified in the row above it\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A user-specified command (batch script, Windows/DOS executable, etc.) may be ran at the conclusion of a sequence. This command may be specified under {\b Options > Imaging > Sequence}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Sequence Gain and Offset settings can now be entered without having any camera connected. The values will be validated on sequence start in case an incompatible value was specified\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The pre-sequence checklist has been enhanced to check whether the telescope is parked. If it is parked, and the user affirms the action, N.I.N.A. will unpark the telescope before beginning the sequence\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added a pre-sequence check to ensure that enough disk space is available to store the whole sequence\u8217's amount of images. The calculation does not take any file compression into account as that is unpredictable.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab End of Sequence operations are now done in parallel\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The \u8220"Auto-focus after % HFR Change\u8221" option has been enhanced to not be triggered by a single bad frame which might have been caused by a temporary condition such as wind or a passing vibration\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Auto-focus after % HFR Change\u8221" now resets its reference index on sequence start, a target change, or any auto-focus operation that is caused by other criteria\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Auto-focus After Number of Exposures\u8221" now correctly triggers after the specified number of exposures\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When the camera fails to indicate that an image is available for download after exposure time + 15 seconds, the exposure will be canceled and skipped\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When using filter offsets, NINA will no longer pause a sequence for any specified focuser settle time if there was no change in the focuser\u8217's position after switching filters\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Camera Gain and Offset are now saved as integers and are no longer saved with decimal places\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added estimated target start and end times to sequence view. This is useful for multi-target sequence sets\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Guiding was improperly stopped when performing an auto-focus operation at start of sequence, even if the Disable Guiding option was false\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Sequence file names are now saved with valid file name characters. Invalid characters are replaced with a hyphen (-)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Various sequence window presentation and layout improvements\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab HFR calculation is enforced for light frames when autofocus after HFR change is enabled to ensure that the trigger will always work\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Plate Solving\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Additional information has been added to the plate solve pop-up window that appears during sequencing\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A camera gain and binning setting may be configured for use during automated plate solves\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Removed the \u8220"Repeat until\u8221" option from the {\b Imaging > Plate Solve} tool window. This action will be always occur when \u8220"Reslew to Target\u8221" is enabled\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Plate solvers will now receive an unstretched FITS image instead of a JPEG. This can allow for a quicker and more reliable solve result\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Any {\f1 WARNING} FITS keyword that a plate solver inserts into a solved image will result in a warning notice in N.I.N.A. that contains the keyword\u8217's text\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A custom Astrometry.net API URL may be configured\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Improved status feedback and logging for Astrometry.net plate solve jobs\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Plate Solving window\u8217's Sync and Reslew settings will be saved\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Reworked the plate solving code completely for cleaner operations\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Guiding\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Improved the resiliency of StartGuider when PHD2 is unable to detect a guide star when guiding is started due to temporary clouds or other factors. An auto-retry mechanism has been added to command PHD2 to attempt to select guide star after a configurable timeout\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The guiding graph will now pause during dithering to avoid displaying guide pulses that are not actual corrections\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The guiding graph now displays a gray triangle icon along the X axis at the point where a dither action occurred\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The drawing of lines in the guiding graph will now pause when guiding itself is paused\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The scaling of lines in the guiding graph will now be consistent even if there are missing data points\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Guiding graph settings are now stored in the profile and are loaded when application is started\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Framing Wizard\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab NASA Sky Survey images now are automatically adjusted for brightness and contrast, depending on each image\u8217's characteristics\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When importing FITS or XISF files, any metadata they contain concerning the RA and declination of the image will be used to hint the plate solver. This can drastically speed up the importing of images into the Framing Wizard by avoiding blind solves\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If a FITS or XISF file contains WCS (World Coordinate System) information due to it already being plate solved externally, Framing Wizard will now retrieve and use that information instead of running its own plate solve on the image, resulting in instant positioning and rendering of the image\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The font size of the mosaic panel ID numbers is now scaled based on the imaging rectangle size and zoom level\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Coordinate input fields in the Framing Assistant and Sequence windows now allow for {\f1 -0} to be entered for declination\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When loading an image file into the Framing Assistant, the rectangle dimensions are now correctly calculated\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Device-related improvements\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The following camera settings are now saved to the active profile: USB Limit, Offset, Gain, Binning, Readout Mode, Temperature, Cooling and Warming Duration\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Images from OSC cameras now use their advertised bayer pattern instead of RGGB being assumed all the time\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab N.I.N.A.\u8217's camera simulator will now assume the pixel size, bayer matrix, and sensor temperature attributes of any FITS or XISF file that is loaded into it\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The equatorial system reported by the mount driver is now used, and the Epoch setting under {\b Options > General > Astrometry} has been removed. N.I.N.A. will default to J2000 when a mount\u8217's driver reports an epoch of \u8220"other\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Wait and check to see if the mount flipped automatically at the meridian when \u8220"Use Telescope Side of Pier\u8221" is on\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A short timeout after mount sync operations has been added as some mounts may not immediately report updated coordinates after a Sync command is sent to them\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab N.I.N.A.\u8217's File Camera can now watch folders for Sony\u8217's {\f1 .ARW} and Olympus\u8217' {\f1 .ORF} RAW file formats\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Reintroduced a \u8220"No Guider\u8221" option under the {\b Equipment > Guiding} device list so that unguided setups do not suffer through unwanted PHD2 executions or unnecessary errors when the \u8220"Connect All Devices\u8221" button is pressed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When a sequence is in the centering stage, rotators will now rotate to nearest orientation even if it results in an image that is upside down. An image\u8217's vertical orientation is not relevant for framing due to the corrective action of star alignment in post-processing\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Focuser control buttons are now disabled while the focuser is reporting that it is moving\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A new option is available to prevent sending any Sync command to the mount. The centering logic will then use offset a coordinate calculation instead. This new logic will also be called when a Sync command fails\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added button to the {\b Equipment > Telescope} window to set the current position of the mount to be its park position. This button is available only if the connected mount\u8217's ASCOM driver supports setting a park position\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Canon camera support has been improved and many common errors have been fixed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Atik cameras that have mechanical shutters will now close those shutters when taking BIAS, DARK, or DARKFLAT images\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab FLI cameras no longer sit idle for the length of the exposure time prior to actually initiating the exposure\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab QHY native camera driver now retrieves only the non-overscan area (the \u8220"effective area\u8221") of the sensor by default. A Camera option now exists to include the overscan area, if desired\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab QHY native camera driver now supports selecting readout modes if the camera offers any\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab QHY cameras that have mechanical shutters will now close those shutters when taking BIAS, DARK, or DARKFLAT images\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab QHY native camera driver now optimizes image file size based on the actual image dimensions, resulting in slightly smaller image file sizes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Binned exposures now finish on QHY cameras that have overscan areas\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab ZWO cameras now properly handle odd bin dimensions (e.g.\u160?3x3)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added a bit scaling option under {\b Options > Equipment > Camera > Advanced Settings}, intended for users of Altair Astro, Omegon, and ToupTek cameras, to bit-shift the raw sub-16 bit data camera data that N.I.N.A. receives to 16 bits in order to improve file compatibility with other capture software\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab FreeImage library upgraded to 3.18 for improved DSLR raw file display\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab ZWO cameras now write correct EGAIN values when switching Gain\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab ZWO cameras reset the FLIP STATUS to NONE in case it was altered by another software\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Time to meridian flip is displayed in telescope windows when enabled\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Imaging window changes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added more southern hemisphere stars to the Manual Focus Stars tool\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Zooming to high magnification inside the Image viewer will no longer show smeared pixels. Sharp pixel edges will be shown instead\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The mid-tone stretch algorithm no longer inverts blown-out pixels\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The HFR History graph now displays indicators that denote when an auto-focus operation has occurred. Hovering over an indicator with the mouse pointer will reveal details for that operation, including the previous focuser position, the newly calculated focuser position, and the focuser\u8217's temperature at the time\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Optimal Exposure Calculator (OEC) has been moved out of the statistics window and into its own tool window for improved user experience, with improved calculations\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab OEC can now load SharpCap Sensor Analysis files to populate fields for the camera\u8217's full well and read noise parameters with measured values\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The camera snapshot control window will now save its parameters across application sessions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added a layout reset button for the Imaging window, located at {\b Options > Imaging > Layout}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Images from OSCs are no longer debayered for presentation twice\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Planetarium software integration\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab All Planetarium options have been moved to their own section in the {\b Options > Equipment} tab and the {\b Options > Planetarium} tab has been removed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When using Stellarium, N.I.N.A. now takes current view\u8217's center coordinates when no target is selected\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added an option to retrieve the coordinates of the center of the sky chart instead of any selected object when using TheSkyX\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Increased reliability when parsing coordinates that are retrieved from Cartes du Ciel and Stellarium, especially in cases where the user\u8217's locale uses characters other than the decimal point as the decimal separator\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Reworked the Planetarium interfacing to be more robust\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 FITS and XISF support\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab XISF files may be created with optional compression or shuffled compression of the image data using the LZ4, LZ4-HC, or ZLib (deflate) lossless compression algorithms. Decompression of compressed XISF files is also supported\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab XISF files may be created with optional embedded checksums of the image data using SHA1, SHA-256, or SHA-512 hashing algorithms. Checksums are verified when opening a XISF file that includes one\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Opening XISF and FITS files that have non-16 bit data is now supported. This benefits the Framing Wizard and N.I.N.A. Simulator Camera\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab XISF image properties for aperture and focal length now correctly state values in meters rather than millimeters\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 File name patterns and FITS keywords\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 $$DATEMINUS12$$}: Shifts the current date and time to 12 hours into the past. This allows for all images from a day-crossing session to be saved into the same date folder\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 $$READOUTMODE$$}: Allows the camera\u8217's readout mode to be used in file or folder names\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 $$SQM$$}: Allows the current reading from an attached sky quality meter to be used in file or folder names\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 $$USBLIMIT$$}: Allows the USB Limit setting for the camera, if available, to be use in file or folder names\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The {\f1 $$FRAMENR$$} pattern now creates a 4 digit number, padding with zeros. Example: {\f1 0004}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The \u8220"Image File Pattern\u8221" setting will now correctly save its state to the active profile when file patterns are dragged from the list into the \u8220"Image File Pattern\u8221" field\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A new example preview of the currently-assembled file pattern appears below the \u8220"Image File Pattern\u8221" field. Any folder separators that are specified are denoted by a {\f1 \u8250?} character\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab File pattern values are now scrubbed for leading and trailing white spaces and other illegal characters to prevent the creation of an invalid file or folder name\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added the {\f1 READOUTM} keyword to FITS and XISF files to record the name of the readout mode used to create the image\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added the {\f1 BAYERPAT}, {\f1 XBAYEROFF}, and {\f1 YBAYEROFF} keywords to FITS and XISF files when using color cameras. A menu under {\b Options > Equipment > Camera} allows the user to override the driver-specified Bayer pattern with an alternative pattern. This allows for automatic debayering in some processing applications, including the use of the \u8220"Auto\u8221" setting in PixInsight\u8217's Debayer process.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added the {\f1 USBLIMIT} keyword to FITS and XISF files to record the USB Limit setting of the camera\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The FITS {\f1 XPIXSZ} and {\f1 YPIXSZ} keywords (and related XISF properties) now correctly account for the binning factor\sa180\par}
