{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Version 1.9\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Features\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Camera Control\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Native support for Finger Lakes Instrumentation ProLine/MicroLine cameras and color filter wheels\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Switch Hubs\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A new equipment type \u8220"Switch\u8221" has been added which can connect to an AscomSwitch or to a PrimaLuceLab EAGLE PC\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Dither without guiding\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A new Direct Guider has been added, which doesn\u8217't require a guide camera. It can only perform random dithers. It connects directly to the telescope, and will if required perform a dither via a Pulse Guide of a user-provided duration in a random direction.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Enhanced direct guider will accept decimal durations (e.g.\u160?0.5s), and perform random angle selection in a way that minimizes target deviation from center, even after many dither operations.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Plate Solving\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added interface for ASTAP, the Astrometric STAcking Program, astrometric solver and FITS viewer as a plate solver\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Mid-sequence plate solve operations (when slewing to target, or after Meridian Flip) have been enhanced to have the following behavior:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab If plate solve fails, it automatically falls back to blind failover\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab If blind failover also fails, plate solve can be set to await a certain time period (by default 10 minutes) before trying again, up to a certain number of attempts (user-defined)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab If all attempts fail, or Meridian is getting close, plate solve will be considered failed, but sequence will continue as usual\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added options to adjust downsample factor and maximum number of considered stars for ASTAP and local astrometry.net solvers\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 GPS Assisted Location\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added a NMEA GPS interface to retrieve the current location\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Interfacing with planetarium programs\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab NINA can interface with Cartes du Ciel, HNSKY, Stellarium, and TheSkyX through their repsective TCP services to import the selected object for use in the Sequence Editor and Framing Assistant, as well as setting the observing location to match that which is set in those programs\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Manual Camera\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Inside the camera selection there is a new entry for \u8220"Manual Camera\u8221".\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab This simulated camera will enable the use of cameras which lack an SDK, while still using the whole N.I.N.A. workflow.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab It will watch a specified folder for newly created files. These files will be stored inside an internal queue.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Each time the application wants to download an exposure from the camera, the first item of this file queue is resolved and loaded into N.I.N.A.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Additionally a manual Bulb Mode trigger can be activated, so it will use the selected Bulb Mode in Settings->Equipment->Camera on Exposure Start.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When this trigger is deactivated the application will just skip the Start Exposure and wait for another file to roll into the specified folder\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Weather data sources\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The existing OpenWeatherMap implementation has been replaced with a full weather data interface.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The new interface allows devices with ASCOM ObservingConditions class drivers to supply N.I.N.A. with weather data and other conditions.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Native OpenWeatherMap functionality is maintained, and any configured OWM API key is retained and utilized by the new native OWM client.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Weather data sources are now configured under the Equipment section.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Any available weather data types (air temperature, pressure, wind speed, etc.) are inserted into images as FITS keywords and/or XISF image properties.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Focusing\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Quick focuser movement buttons have been added (fine/coarse move IN/OUT) to the focuser views\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A new focuser settle time parameter has been added, in case the focuser shifts the image when moving (SCT, lens belt focusing, etc.). This should help with auto-focus in particular.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Backlash can be compensated using two methods. Absolut and Overshoot. Absolut will add absolute backlash values to the movement while overshoot will overshoot the position by a larger amount and move backwards again.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Focuser backlash (in and out) can now be specified. The backlash will be applied to focuser movements depending on the method specified.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Sequence Auto-Focus can now be triggered if measured HFR of any frame is X% worse than the first frame taken after the previous auto-focus routine.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab More resilient autofocus:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Ability to automatically reattempt autofocus from scratch several times in case it failed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Automatically go back to original focus position if obtained HFR is significantly worse than original\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Ability to take multiple autofocus exposures per focus point and average their HFR. This leads to smoother autofocus curves.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab A crop ratio has been added to the autofocus, letting users autofocus only on the center of the frame\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Autofocus can now be set to use only the top brightest stars, so the same stars are used throughout the autofocus routine. This will work best on sparse star fields, and for stable, well-aligned equipment (e.g.\u160?so stars don\u8217't move between auto-focus exposures)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Ability to use binning for autofocus\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Sequencing\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab End of Sequence Options are now available, which include:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Parking the telescope - This will stop the guiding, and invoke the mount Park method if available, otherwise the mount will slew to near the celestial pole (on the same side of Meridian it last was) and stop tracking. {\b Before using this in production, test out the feature at the telescope, with your finger on the power switch. This is to avoid any crash into the pier for mounts that do not have limits.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Warming the camera - the camera will be slowly cooled, with the cooler eventually turned off\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A pre-sequence check is now triggered, and will notify end users of a variety of potential issues (camera not cooled yet, guider not connected, telescope not connected but slew enabled, etc.) at sequence start\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab It is now possible to reset the progress of a sequence item, or of a whole sequence target. If an item that occurred prior to the active sequence item is reset, stopping and starting the sequence will get back to it, but pausing/playing will keep going from the current item.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The sequence start button is unavailable if an imaging loop is in progress in the imaging tab\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If telescope is capable of reporting SideOfPier there will now be a new option to consider this for calculating the need for meridian flips\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab It is now possible to set the Offset in addition to the Gain within each sequence item\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added buttons to move sequence row up and down the list\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab File handling now changed so that:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab the default folder for sequences is set under Options -> Imaging\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab a \u8216'modified\u8217' status is maintained for each target\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab targets can be loaded from any xml file\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab targets can be saved back to the file it was loaded from\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab a \u8216'Save as\u8217' option is added to save to a new file\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab a warning is issued if a target is closed without saving when it has been modified. This also applies when the application is closed.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Controls to change order of targets in a multi-target sequence\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Ability to save and load \u8216'target sets\u8217' (a set of targets in a certain sequence)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Flat Wizard\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Progress bars have been added for remaining filters and exposures\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A new Slew to Zenith button has been added for easier flats. This includes an option for east or west pier side, depending on which side of pier the mount should approach zenith from.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A new option to pause between filters has been added. This is to allow the user the chance to set lightbox settings\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Interface\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Imaging tab - Equipment specific views will only show the \u8220"Connected\u8221" flag when the device is not connected to save space\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added a layout reset button to the imaging tab to restore the default dock layout.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Equipment chooser dropdowns are now grouped by driver categories to easily distinguish between for example ASCOM drivers and other vendor drivers\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 File Handling\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab All FITS keywords now have descriptive comments with units of measurement noted if applicable\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab FITS keyword {\f1 DATE-OBS} now has millisecond resolution, eg: {\f1 2019-03-24T04:04:55.045}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Additional FITS keywords are now added to images if their associated data is available:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\f1 DATE-LOC}: Date and time of exposure adjusted for local time\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\f1 FOCRATIO}: Focal ratio of the telescope, user-configurable under Options->Equipment->Telescope\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\f1 SET-TEMP}: The configured CCD cooling setpoint\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\f1 SITEELEV}: Elevation of the observing site, in meters\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\f1 SWCREATE}: Contains {\f1 N.I.N.A. <version> <architecture>}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\f1 TELESCOP}: Telescope name if provided under Options->Equipment->Telescope. Falls back to ASCOM mount driver name\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 OSC Camera Handling\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Debayering is now applied prior to plate-solving or auto-focus star detection\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab An Unlinked Stretch option has been added. When enabled, color channels will be stretched separately, helping hide the sky background. This results in more visible celestial objects, and helps enhance both autofocus and platesolving reliablity, especially in light polluted areas. Processing time is however increased.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A Debayered HFR option has been added. When enabled, the HFR computation will be made on the Debayered image rather than the Bayered array, providing better Auto-focus results\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Star Detection Sensitivity\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Star Detection has been enhanced to detect more stars more accurately, while avoiding picking up noise by checking that the star is a local maximum and has sufficient bright pixels\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab In addition, a new Star Sensitivity Parameter is available in the Imaging options. It has three settings:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Normal: use standard NINA star detection\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab High: More sensitive method, with little to no performance impact. Typically picks up 1.5x - 2.5x more stars than Normal\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Highest: Most sensitive method, with some performance impact. Typically picks up 1.5x - 2.5x more stars than High\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The higher the detection level, the more likely lumps of noise are liable to be picked up (despite rejection parameters to avoid that)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A noise reduction parameter has been added for better star detection in fairly noisy images, which can be important if using High or Highest star sensitivity levels, although the Normal sensitivity level will also benefit from it. Several settings are available:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab None: no noise reduction on full size image done before star detection\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Median: a Median filter is applied to the full size image before star detection. This is good if the sensor has many hot pixels, but time consuming\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Normal: a standard fast Gaussian filter is applied to the full size image before star detection. This is good for smoothing out the thermal and bias noise of the sensor\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab High: a strong fast Gaussian filter is applied to the full size image before star detection. This is for fairly noisy images, but can make star detection more difficult\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Highest: a very strong fast Gaussian filter is applied to the full size image before star detection. This is for noisy images, although star detection may suffer\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Bugfixes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fixed when FramingAssistant was not opened before and a DSO was selected from the SkyAtlas as Framing Source an error could occur\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fixed scrolling through Framing Assistant Offline Sky Map while cursor was inside Rectangle ignored zooming\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fixed Alitude charts displaying wrong Twilight/Night predictions for some scenarios\par}
